    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.0-dev-538+gf9c62ce34\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavour OS \n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20221119-145034-49b9839f, alacritty 0.11.0 (8dbaa0bb)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR, bob, rhysd/action-setup-vim\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:setglobal signcolumn=yes\r\n:lua= vim.opt_global.signcolumn:get()\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nReturns \"yes\".\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nReturns \"auto\", its default.\r\n\r\nBoth `:setglobal signcolumn?` and `:lua= vim.go.signcolumn` returns \"yes\", and the bug doesn't happen on v0.8.1.\r\n\r\nIt only happens with \"local to window\" option like \"wrap\", not with \"global or local to window\" option like \"scrolloff\".",
