            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "i looked at the regression found by @zeertzjq in #21382 and have the following thoughts:\r\n\r\n#21382 closes #18255 which tries to achieve this: global-local options do not have a local value in some cases and then opt_local:append() should copy and extend the global value as vimscript += would. However, as there is no local value, this didn't happen. The patch fixed this by making opt_local fall back to the global value.\r\n\r\nThe problem with the patch is that now getting options with vim.opt[_local|_global] always ignores the scope info.\r\n\r\nInstead it should check whether the passed scope is local and the option a global-local, and only then not pass a scope to vim.api.nvim_get_option_value()\r\n\r\nimo\r\n\r\n@phelipetls @lewis6991\r\n",
