        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Just created a patch to try to address this: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/25196.\r\n\r\n> Instead it should check whether the passed scope is local and the option a global-local, and only then not pass a scope to vim.api.nvim_get_option_value()\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what you meant by checking if \"the option a global-local\" but my reasoning was that we should use as initial value a global-local value for `vim.opt` and `vim.opt_local` and global value for `vim.opt_global`.\r\n\r\nThe previous patch tried to address that `vim.opt_local` used local value when in fact it should have used a global-local value (i.e., should not have passed a `{ scope = \"local\" }` to `api.nvim_get_option_value`).\r\n\r\nBut obviously, in hindsight, it was a mistake to not pass `{ scope = \"global\" }` in the case of `vim.opt_global`.",
